properties.headline: High Wind Watch issued January 31 at 2:12PM PST until February 3 at 12:00PM PST by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Northwest winds 30 to 40 mph with gusts up to 60 mph
possible.

* WHERE...Santa Clarita Valley.

* WHEN...From Sunday afternoon through Monday morning.

* IMPACTS...Damaging winds could blow down large objects such as
trees and power lines. Power outages are possible. Travel
could be difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Interstate 5 and Highways 126 and 14 will
be affected.
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WATCH IN EFFECT FROM SUNDAY AFTERNOON THROUGH MONDAY MORNING
